HEADWORD: Peritoneum
<hw>Per`i*to*ne"um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>peritoneum</ets>, <ets>peritonaeum</ets>, Gr. <?/, <?/, fr. <?/ to
stretch all around or over; <grk>peri`</grk> around + <?/ to
stretch.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The smooth serous membrane which
lines the cavity of the abdomen, or the whole body cavity when there is
no diaphragm, and, turning back, surrounds the viscera, forming a
closed, or nearly closed, sac.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>periton⟦ae⟧um</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peritonitis</ent>⟦br⟧
